All cypriniform fishes lack pharyngobranchial tooth plates (
Fink & Fink, 1981
). At least one pharyngobranchial toothplate is present in all outgroup taxa examined.

63. Gill-raker teeth (
Johnson & Patterson, 1997
): (0) present; (1) absent (CI = 0.50; RI = 0.50).

All cypriniform fishes lack gill-raker teeth (
Johnson & Patterson, 1997
; 
Fig. 31B–D
). Tiny teeth are associated with the gill rakers of all outgroup taxa examined (
Fig. 31A
), excluding 

Denticeps clupeoides

.

66. Gill-filament ossifications (
Conway & Mayden, 2010
): (0) absent; (1) present (CI = 1.00; RI = 1.00).

In members of the 
Cobitidae
, hypobranchial 3 is closely associated with its antimere along the midline, forming a concave facet in which the posteriormost tip of basibranchial 3 articulates (
Fig. 30I, J
). In some cobitid species a single hypobranchial-3 element is present (
Conway & Mayden, 2007
), presumably the result of ontogenetic fusion between the pair of hypobranchial 3 ossifications (
Fig. 30I, J
). The posteriormost tip of basibranchial 3 articulates with this single hypobranchial 3 element in these later species in a similar manner. In other cypriniform fishes and in outgroup taxa an articulation between hypobranchial 3 and basibranchial 3 is absent (
Figs 10
, 
30A–H, K–O
).

In members of the genus 

Psilorhynchus

hypobranchial 2 is absent, and is represented only by its cartilaginous precursor, hypobranchial2 cartilage (
Conway & Mayden, 2007
; 
Fig. 10
). In other cypriniform fishes and in outgroup taxa hypobranchial 2 is present (
Fig. 30
).

In the labeonine cyprinids the anterior edge of epibranchial 1 exhibits a large, heavily fenestrated flange of membrane bone, which extends far anterior of the main shaft of the bone (
Fig. 32A–C
). This flange probably provides some degree of support to the vomeropalatal organ, present on the dorsal surface of the oral cavity in these fishes (
Reid, 1982
; 
Stiassny & Getahun, 2007
). In other cypriniform fishes and in outgroup taxa the anterior edge of epibranchial 1
